Typical delay duration is derived by calculating the average delay time based on the percentage of flights delayed by various time periods. The percentages are directly interpreted as contributing to the average delay time in minutes. ;
The given percentages in the database columns represent the distribution of delays across different time intervals for the flights. ;
Although percentages are used to represent delay intervals, for the purpose of this calculation, they are treated as contributing directly to an average delay time in minutes.

sql:
SELECT SUM(total_flights) AS total_flights, AVG(avg_delay_mins) AS avg_delay_mins
FROM flight_performance
WHERE airport_id = 0;
